@Barry Ancona

The original comment, whether ironic or not, and your response to it remind me of the odd phrase "essential oil" and how it became ubiquitous about 7 years ago, when colleagues would have essential oil diffusers in their offices, that made everything smell of ginger or vanilla or mint.  Pleasant, at first, but after a while...enough!

As someone who spends a good bit of time thinking philosophically, I found it amusing to think that the "essence" of a thing could be extracted and magically preserved in an oil.

That the OP confuses it, intentionally or not, with a necessary part of the treatment of a condition adds another layer of amusement to the phrase.
Enough with "essential oils"!

